The other girl who I assume helps the chefs, stomps around and moves quickly but actually doesn’t do anything. She had the worst customer service and hygiene, I would compare to a moody teenager. - The above mentioned moody teenager, bites her fingers constantly, then uses those said fingers to sprinkle cheese on peoples meals. I watched in disbelief. - For a takeaway vendor, meals are fast. My 1 pasta meal, with no meat. Took 35 minutes. The moody teenager with the hygiene issue told me at 19 minutes it would be 4 more minutes which is fine, but it ended up being 35 minutes total. When I asked why it’s taking longer, the response I got was ‘the kitchen got messed up’. Then when I saw the moody teenager with the hygiene issue put my food together, she forgot the burrata added to my meal that I had paid extra for. If I hadn’t watched the process, I would’ve walked away with part missing. When i had told her to check the burrata was there, the moody teenager didn’t respond, just stormed off to add it.... really odd considering she made a mistake. When she gave me the food she just pushed it at me without eye contact.  The food itself was good. But for the experience I went through, I wouldn’t go again. I don’t usually leave reviews and I left it till the next day and it’s still bothering me so I’m leaving this now. Ultimately, I hope these girls get customer service and hygiene training.
